      "content": "it just feels like putting a bandaid on a gunshot wound. people keep saying things will get better or i'll find resilience, but they don't get it. the debt isn't going away and the reputation is gone. if i stay, i just have to keep living in this nightmare of what i lost every single day. sometimes it feels like the only way to actually escape the feeling of being a failure is to just... not be here to feel it anymore. like, isn't there just a more permanent way to make the shame stop?",
